    {
        "content": "<p>I don't follow. We need the following:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>A global <code>IsROrC ‚ÑÇ</code> instance.</li>\n<li>With the change in this PR, a global <code>PartialOrder ‚ÑÇ</code> instance (because <code>IsROrC</code> now extends <code>PartialOrder</code>)</li>\n</ol>\n<p>At that point, all the data is in global instances, so why should instances that only add proofs be scoped?</p>",
